Sooo I finally went and did it!!!! ..Set up a new music studio in my unfinished basement. M Audio Code 49 Midi Controller with 49 keys and 16 pads. A Mac Mini with two monitors. NT1 Cardioid Condenser Mic with shock mount and popshield. A Focusrite Scarlett 2i2 audio interface. 2 JBL LSR308 Studio Monitors. Logic Pro X recording / mixing software. A Ditto X2 Looper for my Stingray (bass). Also an MXR Bass D.I. ...Everything I need for now to do some magical musical stuff and I can always expand and upgrade if'n I want. Seriously excited. Housing costs can consume the biggest share of your paycheck, regardless of where in the world you live. According to a report done by Deutsche Bank, the average rent for a two-bedroom apartment in some of the world's largest cities can vary from $300 in Bangalore, India, to more than $3,400 in San Francisco, California. Ranked at number 11, Singapore had an average rent cost of $1,884 a month, for a pad located in the hub of this electric city.
